cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on visual recognition tasks, specifically long-tailed data distribution, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and learning strategy, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of re-weighting and re-sampling, which are common techniques in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
